The paper focuses on improving object detection using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves boosting, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG) and also involves using learned representations (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates its performance on a benchmark dataset (cs.MM) and discusses the limitations of current methods (cs.IR).
